            </did>
            <c02 level="class">
               <did>
                  <unitid type="work">poems.sng1</unitid>
                  <unittitle type="uniform" label="Uniform Title:">
                     <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Song I</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unittitle label="First Line:">
                     <title linktype="simple">'Midst beauty and pleasure's gay triumphs, to languish</title>
                  </unittitle>
                  <unitdate normal="1797" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1797</unitdate>
               </did>
               <bibliography>
                  <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#S/H_1966"
                          linktype="simple">Starr/Hendrickson (eds.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Complete Poems</title> (1966),  99</bibref>
                  <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblp.shtml#LoR_1969"
                          linktype="simple">Lonsdale (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Poems</title> (1969),  240-241</bibref>
               </bibliography>
               <scopecontent>
                  <p>Written before <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/table.shtml#1761"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <date normal="176110" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">October 1761</date>
                     </extref> at the request
							of <persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771" source="lcnaf">Gray</persname>'s friend <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Speed, Henrietta Jane, 1728-1783"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Speed, Henrietta Jane,          1728-1783">Henrietta Speed</persname>
                     </extref>. 
							<extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Walpole, Horace, 1717-1797"
                             show="replace"
                             linktype="simple">
                        <persname normal="Walpole, Horace,          1717-1797">Walpole</persname>
                     </extref> transcribed and sent it in a
							letter to Caroline Campbell, Countess	of Ailesbury, <date normal="17611128" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">28 November 1761</date>.
							First published, beginning "With beauty, with pleasure surrounded,
							to languish", in Pope's <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Works</title> (1797),
							ed. Joseph Warton, vol. II,  285n. Entitled <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Amatory Lines</title> by <persname normal="Mitford, John, 1781-1859">Mitford</persname> and <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#NoC_1917"
                             linktype="simple"> Northup, <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Bibliography</title> (1917), <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/cgi-bin/view.cgi?collection=secondary&amp;edition=NoC_1917&amp;page=61"
                                show="replace"
                                linktype="simple">61</extref>
                     </bibref>.
							</p>
               </scopecontent>
