                  </did>
                  <bibliography>
                     <bibref title="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/biblb.shtml#SmM_1989"
                             linktype="simple">Smith (ed.), <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Index</title> (1989), item GrT 126,  91</bibref>
                     <bibref title="" linktype="simple">Richardson, Gayle M., "HM 12550". E-mail
								to the editor, 15 November 2006</bibref>
                  </bibliography>
                  <scopecontent>
                     <p>Transcript in an unidentified hand, untitled and beginning "With
								beauty with pleasure surrounded to languish", together with <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/findingaid/mss.0159.xml">MS 0159</extref>, annotated in	the hand of <extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Walpole, Horace, 1717-1797"
                                show="replace"
                                linktype="simple">
                           <persname normal="Walpole, Horace,           1717-1797">Horace Walpole</persname>
                        </extref> "The following two
								poems were given to Mr. Jacob by (<extref href="https://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Speed, Henrietta Jane, 1728-1783"
                                show="replace"
                                linktype="simple">
                           <persname normal="Speed, Henrietta Jane, 1728-1783">Miss 
										Speed</persname>
                        </extref>) Countess of Vim, who told
								him they (were) written by <persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771">Mr. Gray</persname>".
							</p>
                  </scopecontent>
